01:02.020 --> 01:03.977
Hail Mary, full of grace,

01:04.063 --> 01:05.474
The Lord is with thee.

01:05.566 --> 01:07.603
Blessed art thou amongst women,

01:07.693 --> 01:10.310
blessed is the fruit of thy womb, Jesus.

01:10.404 --> 01:12.191
Holy Mary, Mother of God,

01:12.281 --> 01:13.362
pray for us sinners,

01:13.448 --> 01:15.155
now and at the hour of our death.

01:15.242 --> 01:17.154
Amen.

01:53.322 --> 01:54.312
Hello?

01:57.409 --> 01:58.399
Hey.

02:00.746 --> 02:02.408
There's a switch right behind your head

02:02.497 --> 02:03.704
- if you want...
- Switch?

02:03.790 --> 02:04.871
The switch for the light.

02:04.958 --> 02:06.324
It's right behind your head
if you want to...

02:06.418 --> 02:08.785
Oh. I'm good.

02:09.880 --> 02:10.791
Okay.

02:16.845 --> 02:18.802
- Whenever you're ready.
- Okay.

02:18.889 --> 02:22.098
Aren't you supposed to, like,
ask me for a sin list

02:22.184 --> 02:24.346
and call me a child
or a lamb or some shit?

02:25.020 --> 02:28.058
Thing. Something. Sorry.

02:28.899 --> 02:30.106
It's your first time?

02:30.192 --> 02:31.308
How did you guess?

02:33.236 --> 02:34.818
There aren't any real rules to this.

02:35.280 --> 02:36.316
I'm just here to help.

02:36.907 --> 02:38.569
With what, exactly?

02:38.659 --> 02:40.116
Your relationship with God.

02:40.202 --> 02:42.410
Oh...

02:43.747 --> 02:44.658
Sorry.

02:45.082 --> 02:46.539
Again.

02:46.625 --> 02:48.241
Don't apologize. This is for you.

02:51.421 --> 02:52.332
Okay.

02:53.715 --> 02:56.253
Well, thing is...

02:57.010 --> 02:58.000
I'm dying.

03:03.141 --> 03:04.052
I'm sorry.

03:05.435 --> 03:06.721
You're probably thinking,

03:07.145 --> 03:09.933
this chick's trying to clear the deck
at the last minute or whatever,

03:10.023 --> 03:13.858
you know, hit the redo button
on the way out, but...

03:13.944 --> 03:15.105
I'm not here to judge you.

03:15.195 --> 03:17.232
And that's great, and everything,

03:17.322 --> 03:19.359
but I'm really not here
to save my own ass.

03:19.449 --> 03:22.567
I'm here for a practical reason
as opposed to spiritual.

03:22.661 --> 03:23.492
What would that be?

03:23.578 --> 03:24.614
Funeral arrangements.

03:25.080 --> 03:26.742
This isn't usually how that...

03:26.832 --> 03:29.370
I'm sure you've got a guy
I'm supposed to call...

03:30.168 --> 03:32.956
or maybe a website.

03:33.672 --> 03:35.504
I just... I don't know
how much time I have left,

03:35.590 --> 03:39.004
and I really don't want to spend it
planning an event

03:39.094 --> 03:40.881
I'm not even going to be able to attend.

03:43.598 --> 03:45.180
I want a nice casket.

03:47.519 --> 03:51.729
Nothing too over the top,
but not boring either.

03:54.985 --> 03:56.977
The kind of casket
that makes people think,

03:57.863 --> 04:00.731
"Wow, it's a shame she died so young."

04:02.909 --> 04:04.775
But I don't want it to elicit tears.

04:05.120 --> 04:06.031
Just enough...

04:07.414 --> 04:08.325
you know...

04:09.249 --> 04:10.410
whatever you call it...

04:10.751 --> 04:12.413
so they'll miss me in that, um...

04:13.420 --> 04:16.083
that fond memory kind of way.

04:20.969 --> 04:22.210
I really am sorry.

04:23.972 --> 04:24.883
Thank you.

04:26.016 --> 04:27.302
I may have needed this.

04:30.812 --> 04:32.474
Definitely needed something.

04:37.736 --> 04:38.852
This is what I do.

04:39.988 --> 04:43.572
Yeah, well,
this seems to be what I do, too.

04:44.409 --> 04:45.900
As far as pallbearers go,

04:45.994 --> 04:46.984
are those included

04:47.078 --> 04:49.195
or should I make a list of ex-boyfriends

04:49.289 --> 04:50.951
with decent upper-body strength?

04:51.041 --> 04:51.952
Um, I...

04:52.667 --> 04:54.499
- I think that you should probably...
- Screw it.

04:54.586 --> 04:55.576
I'll do cremation.

04:56.421 --> 04:57.457
Thanks again for listening.

05:00.300 --> 05:01.381
You sound nice.

07:19.522 --> 07:21.730
I keep hearing some sort of reverb.

07:21.816 --> 07:23.557
Reverb's not the problem.

07:23.652 --> 07:24.893
It's like a flange or...

07:24.986 --> 07:26.898
- I'm-I'm hearing something.
- There's no flange.

07:27.322 --> 07:28.654
Do you even know what a flange is?

07:28.740 --> 07:32.233
Maybe the problem is that our equipment

07:32.327 --> 07:36.162
happens to amplify
your vocal imperfections.

07:36.247 --> 07:39.661
Full disclosure. I haven't had an
opportunity to read the manual

07:39.751 --> 07:42.960
but I don't think
this piece of equipment comes

07:43.046 --> 07:45.333
with a setting for drowning out jealousy

07:46.091 --> 07:48.048
because I think you're jealous,

07:49.052 --> 07:50.213
is what I'm trying to say.

07:53.515 --> 07:55.051
Of... Of my singing.

08:30.051 --> 08:30.962
Was I flat again?

08:37.017 --> 08:37.928
Hmm.

09:01.458 --> 09:03.324
<i>Death is everywhere.</i>

09:03.418 --> 09:05.000
<i>We can try to run from it,</i>

09:05.086 --> 09:06.327
<i>deny it,</i>

09:06.421 --> 09:07.707
<i>hide away</i>

09:07.797 --> 09:10.540
<i>in the most articulate,
philosophical explanations</i>

09:10.633 --> 09:12.670
<i>that man has been coming up with
since, well...</i>

09:13.636 --> 09:14.547
<i>man.</i>

09:14.929 --> 09:16.761
The Bible certainly has
a lot to say about it.

09:16.848 --> 09:19.591
Trust me, I know. I've skimmed
the book more than a few times.

09:24.814 --> 09:25.804
The truth is...

09:27.901 --> 09:29.984
is that the more I think about death,

09:30.070 --> 09:32.062
the less I seem to really understand it.

09:33.907 --> 09:34.818
And guess what.

09:36.868 --> 09:37.779
That's okay.

09:40.580 --> 09:42.697
Because knowing
that our time here is limited,

09:43.083 --> 09:44.949
that's what makes it matter so much.

09:46.127 --> 09:47.163
Good, Daniel.

09:50.131 --> 09:51.372
Most inspiring one yet.

09:52.634 --> 09:54.000
You don't think it was a little dark?

09:54.511 --> 09:56.423
Well, Matthew made it dark.

09:56.721 --> 09:58.883
You're just commenting on the writing.

09:59.891 --> 10:01.007
You got a gift.

10:02.310 --> 10:05.803
It reminds me
of a younger version of myself.

10:05.897 --> 10:09.311
It doesn't mean they'll laugh
at the Bible skimming bit.

10:09.400 --> 10:10.311
Well, I just thought that...

10:10.401 --> 10:13.644
You thought that it was funny enough
for a laugh pause.

10:13.738 --> 10:17.072
I mean, maybe a slight smile,

10:18.034 --> 10:19.821
a courtesy chuckle,

10:20.328 --> 10:21.318
but a laugh pause?

10:21.412 --> 10:22.619
What if I work on the timing...

10:22.705 --> 10:27.325
I've only been
with this parish for 30 years,

10:27.418 --> 10:29.330
and you, just-just over one.

10:31.464 --> 10:33.706
I'm sure going with your gut
is the right call.

10:37.512 --> 10:39.469
Oh, come on, come on.

10:39.556 --> 10:40.842
What, Father?

10:40.932 --> 10:44.596
Why... even the Franciscans have...
have some rules about... this.

10:45.645 --> 10:46.726
Let me check, Father.

10:49.274 --> 10:50.560
And cometh game day,

10:50.650 --> 10:52.266
'tis okay to go forth

10:52.360 --> 10:55.068
in the colors of thine chosen team

10:55.155 --> 10:57.021
unless thine chosen team

10:57.115 --> 11:00.199
is the Purdue Boilermakers
or the Kentucky Wildcats.

11:01.494 --> 11:02.405
God is good.

11:03.037 --> 11:05.450
Tip off's in five minutes.
I'm making my nachos.

11:07.709 --> 11:10.702
You never told me
how the Friday-night confession went.

11:13.464 --> 11:15.706
Oh, it was... fine.

11:15.800 --> 11:16.711
There was uh...

11:17.552 --> 11:18.463
It was nothing.

11:18.803 --> 11:19.714
It was fine.

11:21.181 --> 11:22.046
Daniel?

11:22.140 --> 11:25.178
Oh, the game's about to start.

11:25.268 --> 11:26.429
I should probably...

11:27.187 --> 11:29.224
He would have been proud
of who you've become.

11:30.064 --> 11:30.975
Your dad.

11:34.694 --> 11:35.901
Have a good night, Father.

11:43.995 --> 11:44.951
Hmm.

11:49.292 --> 11:50.373
Skimmed the book.

11:56.799 --> 11:58.756
<i>Rivers crosses over...</i>

11:59.928 --> 12:02.636
Are you serious? Did you see that?

12:02.722 --> 12:03.929
- Come on!
- Did you see that?

12:04.015 --> 12:07.429
- Shoot the... three pointer.
- For the Love of God.

12:07.518 --> 12:10.135
Basket. Dunk.

12:11.314 --> 12:15.433
Father, you're from here, yes?

12:15.526 --> 12:17.939
- Yeah.
- How do you not love basketball?

12:18.029 --> 12:20.521
I think it's definitely a b...
a good way of...

12:20.615 --> 12:22.652
Okay, okay, okay, okay, tell me this.

12:22.742 --> 12:23.778
W- What's-What's your thing?

12:23.868 --> 12:25.325
- My thing?
- You know, your thing,

12:25.411 --> 12:27.949
like I... I played
third string power forward

12:28.039 --> 12:29.530
on myjunior high basketball team.

12:29.624 --> 12:33.208
I went on to never actually make
another squad after that,

12:33.294 --> 12:36.458
so that now I live through them.

12:36.547 --> 12:38.914
Delusional hoop dreams and saturated fat...

12:39.008 --> 12:40.795
that's my thing. What's yours?

12:40.885 --> 12:43.593
Uh, I... Yeah, I guess, I mean... God.

12:46.474 --> 12:48.306
- God what?
- God's my thing.

12:49.102 --> 12:50.684
What?

12:50.770 --> 12:52.762
- No.
- Why is that... What no?

12:52.855 --> 12:55.814
Look, you gotta... you gotta find
something of your own,

12:55.900 --> 12:58.563
something selfish and stupid and...

12:59.696 --> 13:00.561
human.

13:00.655 --> 13:03.648
Otherwise you just might wind up
like Victor.

13:05.076 --> 13:05.987
What's wrong with that?

13:06.953 --> 13:08.364
He wears his collar to Target.

13:08.454 --> 13:10.320
I mean, he literally puts on his collar

13:10.415 --> 13:12.907
to buy Honey Nut Cheerios
and toilet paper.

13:13.001 --> 13:13.957
Now, that's weird.

13:14.460 --> 13:15.371
That's weird.

13:16.879 --> 13:18.745
Don't... Don't be weird.

13:18.840 --> 13:20.923
And don't bring that shit in the lane!

13:21.009 --> 13:22.966
Oh, do not bring that shit in the lane!

13:23.052 --> 13:24.293
Do not bring that shit in the lane.

13:24.387 --> 13:27.255
- Yeah!
- That's what I am talking about. Okay.

13:27.348 --> 13:28.259
Mm.

13:29.100 --> 13:30.386
Welcome to Hoosier Basketball.

13:31.477 --> 13:32.388
All the best, Father.

15:02.068 --> 15:03.149
Am I late?

15:05.113 --> 15:07.400
I'm sorry, are you lost or...

15:07.490 --> 15:09.152
This is Saint Martin's, right?

15:09.826 --> 15:10.737
Mark's.

15:11.077 --> 15:11.988
I'm Jane.

15:12.286 --> 15:14.619
No, it's Saint Marks. The church.

15:15.623 --> 15:18.331
I'm still Jane. The person.

15:19.419 --> 15:21.206
Daniel. Father Daniel.

15:21.295 --> 15:24.003
- Nice to meet you, Father Daniel.
- Nice to meet you...

15:24.841 --> 15:25.752
Jane.

15:28.052 --> 15:30.920
We're very far apart.

15:34.058 --> 15:35.970
Permission to approach the priest?

15:36.060 --> 15:39.394
Uh, well, you don't really need
to ask permission, but...

15:39.480 --> 15:41.267
it's... okay.

15:41.357 --> 15:43.019
So what's the verdict, Father?

15:43.109 --> 15:44.099
Verdict?

15:44.193 --> 15:45.354
Is it too late?

15:45.445 --> 15:47.186
- For...
- Confession.

15:47.280 --> 15:48.646
- Oh.
- You guys are open late

15:48.739 --> 15:49.570
on Fridays, now, right?

15:49.657 --> 15:52.616
You were the... uh, one from last week.

15:52.702 --> 15:53.613
No.

15:54.370 --> 15:55.281
Yeah.

15:56.247 --> 15:57.158
Maybe.

15:58.416 --> 15:59.327
Yeah.

16:00.376 --> 16:01.366
I recognize your voice.

16:01.461 --> 16:03.953
Distinctive, right? I'm a singer. I sing.

16:04.046 --> 16:05.878
No big deal. I'm good, though.

16:05.965 --> 16:07.501
But let's not make
a whole thing out of it...

16:07.592 --> 16:08.833
Confession was supposed to end
at 2:00 and...

16:08.926 --> 16:10.792
- I can go.
- No, it's just we're very...

16:11.929 --> 16:14.012
- very big on rules around here.
- It's cool. Really.

16:14.098 --> 16:15.805
- And so I think...
- I'll just order some absolution

16:15.892 --> 16:17.975
- with my Taco Bell.
- I meant... Wait, I... I...

16:18.978 --> 16:21.686
I can... I mean, we can...

16:22.482 --> 16:23.518
Thanks, Father.

16:25.860 --> 16:26.771
Daniel.

16:27.487 --> 16:28.648
Can I call you Daniel?

16:31.908 --> 16:33.615
- Uh...
- We'll figure it out in there.

16:52.220 --> 16:54.553
So... maybe we should start talking...

16:54.639 --> 16:56.255
I can't do cremation, Daniel.

16:56.849 --> 16:57.760
I just can't.

16:58.851 --> 17:00.558
I thought about it, and it's like...

17:02.313 --> 17:03.724
what the hell was I thinking?

17:05.775 --> 17:09.644
- Maybe we should start with who your...
- Who's gonna dress me?

17:09.904 --> 17:10.815
What?

17:11.531 --> 17:13.568
Now that we're back
to the standard funeral,

17:13.657 --> 17:15.319
I've got to think about who, you know...

17:16.577 --> 17:19.069
No way I'm letting a creepy funeral-y guy

17:19.163 --> 17:21.576
put me in some kind of sad death smock.

17:21.665 --> 17:23.531
And if my mom got involved...

17:24.752 --> 17:25.663
my God.

17:26.503 --> 17:28.587
She drives one of those Mary Kay cars,

17:28.965 --> 17:30.172
you know, those pink atrocities

17:30.258 --> 17:33.501
they only give
their most celebrated salespeople?

17:35.346 --> 17:38.214
She'd have me wearing a floral pants suit,

17:39.183 --> 17:41.721
and she'd splash so much paint on my face

17:41.811 --> 17:45.350
that I'd look like a transvestite,

17:45.439 --> 17:48.102
prostitute version of Blanche DuBois...

17:48.192 --> 17:49.524
- Why are you here?
- What?

17:51.195 --> 17:53.812
I'm sorry, but last week,

17:53.906 --> 17:55.772
tonight, why?

17:58.244 --> 17:59.075
What do you mean?

17:59.161 --> 18:00.777
Is this really about funeral arrangements?

18:03.249 --> 18:04.615
You don't believe I'm dying?

18:04.709 --> 18:06.291
Wha... that's not what I... I mean...

18:09.964 --> 18:10.875
Are you?

18:13.134 --> 18:14.841
This was a stupid idea.

18:14.927 --> 18:16.384
- Jane...
- I should go.

18:18.931 --> 18:20.342
You came here for a reason.

18:20.766 --> 18:21.677
Here.

18:23.978 --> 18:24.889
Why?

18:34.363 --> 18:35.353
You were open.

18:38.784 --> 18:41.367
And no, I'm not lost,
in case you're wondering.

18:41.454 --> 18:43.320
I'm just... I'm done with it.

18:45.458 --> 18:46.369
I'm done.

18:50.087 --> 18:51.248
Everything around me...

18:51.964 --> 18:52.875
I see it...

18:54.508 --> 18:55.669
and it's all the same.

18:58.888 --> 19:00.220
Nothing.

19:03.267 --> 19:05.975
And it's not that I don't give a shit,
or that I'm giving up.

19:06.937 --> 19:07.848
It's just...

19:08.981 --> 19:10.062
It's disappointing.

19:11.651 --> 19:12.767
No...

19:16.739 --> 19:17.729
heartbreaking.

19:20.826 --> 19:22.237
And there aren't enough cat videos

19:22.328 --> 19:24.820
or fucking TED talks on YouTube
to make up for that.

19:27.875 --> 19:28.865
So when...

19:29.543 --> 19:32.035
faced with all the possible
things left to contemplate...

19:33.381 --> 19:37.842
death feels like one of the
last remaining ideas we have

19:37.927 --> 19:39.884
to... to remind us of...

19:42.098 --> 19:43.009
- of...
- Life?

19:52.024 --> 19:53.856
That light you have outside...

19:53.943 --> 19:54.979
What?

19:55.069 --> 19:56.901
The one over the front door of the church.

19:58.572 --> 20:00.905
It was on when I happened
to walk by last week.

20:00.991 --> 20:01.981
That's why I'm here.

20:10.376 --> 20:12.163
- What about a photo?
- What?

20:12.586 --> 20:13.497
For the funeral.

20:14.338 --> 20:15.920
Sort of a template

20:16.006 --> 20:17.998
for what it is you kind of
want to look like.

20:18.092 --> 20:19.958
- Now, that's not a bad idea.
- Yeah.

20:21.262 --> 20:22.924
You don't think that's too stagey?

20:23.013 --> 20:25.972
Well, the Catholic Church has never
shied away from a little pageantry.

20:26.058 --> 20:27.048
Yeah...

20:27.143 --> 20:29.009
I've seen the crucifix.

20:29.103 --> 20:30.685
- That's not really what I was referring...
- Too soon?

20:32.481 --> 20:33.688
That was kind of too soon.

20:35.609 --> 20:37.942
You gotta wait till at least 3,000 years.

20:38.779 --> 20:41.146
But, I mean, come on.
They put makeup on Jesus.

20:41.574 --> 20:42.815
- No, they don't.
- Yeah, they do.

20:42.908 --> 20:43.944
When do they put makeup on Jesus?

20:44.034 --> 20:45.650
Have you looked at any of the crucifixes

20:45.745 --> 20:46.826
where he's got kind, like, blush on

20:46.912 --> 20:48.198
and some eyeliner?

20:48.289 --> 20:49.825
It's hot in the sun.

20:49.915 --> 20:50.746
Um, no.

20:50.833 --> 20:52.449
They're making him look pretty.

20:52.543 --> 20:55.126
He looks like a woman in some of those.

20:55.463 --> 20:57.125
Which is not all that weird

20:57.214 --> 20:59.126
because, you know, maybe... who knows?

20:59.550 --> 21:01.462
"Hey-soos" would be glad
that you figured it out.

21:01.552 --> 21:03.088
That's how you say His name in Spanish...

21:12.897 --> 21:15.310
"He... He answereth and saith unto them,

21:15.399 --> 21:19.564
"'Let him that hath two coats impart
to him that hath none.

21:19.653 --> 21:21.940
And let him that hath meat...'"

21:22.782 --> 21:24.114
baby, do the same.

21:24.533 --> 21:25.649
Luke 3:11.

21:26.494 --> 21:27.530
How do you like me now?

21:29.121 --> 21:30.032
Father.

21:30.623 --> 21:31.659
Father.

21:35.878 --> 21:37.085
No run today?

21:37.588 --> 21:38.544
I guess I slept in.

21:39.048 --> 21:40.835
- Is everything okay?
- Y-Yeah, yeah.

21:40.925 --> 21:42.632
No, yeah. Just tired.

21:44.178 --> 21:45.089
Victor...

21:46.013 --> 21:47.800
surely you have a verse in there

21:47.890 --> 21:49.597
about the evils of hitting
the snooze button.

21:49.683 --> 21:52.676
Mm-hm. Are the late Fridays
a bit too much?

21:52.770 --> 21:55.183
- No, not at all.
- I'll talk to the Bishop.

21:55.272 --> 21:57.184
No, I-I... you were right.

21:57.274 --> 21:58.981
It's been... It's been really...

21:59.068 --> 22:01.025
It's good. It's very good.

22:01.111 --> 22:02.022
For me.

22:02.822 --> 22:04.154
- Daniel...
- You know, we get to reach out

22:04.240 --> 22:05.356
to different, uh...

22:06.867 --> 22:07.823
So yeah.

22:09.537 --> 22:10.448
Yeah.

22:15.000 --> 22:15.911
Okay.

22:21.215 --> 22:23.548
My problem is that he'll tell his mother

22:23.634 --> 22:25.546
every little detail about our life.

22:25.636 --> 22:29.425
But with me,
it's just I think that he has a problem

22:29.515 --> 22:30.551
with communication.

22:30.641 --> 22:32.883
And that
is what he really needs to work on.

22:32.977 --> 22:34.138
And he knows that already

22:34.228 --> 22:35.639
because I tell him all the time,

22:35.729 --> 22:38.392
but he just goes about his day
like he doesn't even hear me,

22:38.482 --> 22:40.940
which, you can imagine, doesn't feel good

22:41.026 --> 22:43.439
when I'm trying to express my feelings,

22:43.529 --> 22:47.523
which I believe is at the core
of the problem with the marriage,

22:47.616 --> 22:49.653
not to say
that we don't have a good marriage,

22:49.743 --> 22:51.109
because we do.

22:51.203 --> 22:55.163
It's just I thought that if we talked
to someone within the Church,

22:55.249 --> 22:58.538
it might better open up
the lines of communication between...

22:59.378 --> 23:00.494
- Father!
- Yes.

23:01.589 --> 23:02.750
Yes what?

23:07.511 --> 23:09.377
Yes, what he said. Yes.

23:14.977 --> 23:16.388
Yes, I apologized.

23:17.354 --> 23:19.061
I listened to her for another hour...

23:19.148 --> 23:20.184
without interruption...

23:21.191 --> 23:23.524
and of course I assured her
that it would never happen again.

23:24.278 --> 23:25.564
This is not like you.

23:26.322 --> 23:27.358
I know.

23:28.449 --> 23:33.160
We've discussed the importance of detail.

23:35.289 --> 23:38.077
It's the reason why I do even this,

23:38.167 --> 23:41.877
instead of letting
some sacristan housewife...

23:42.796 --> 23:43.707
God bless them...

23:44.340 --> 23:47.549
improperly dress my alter.

23:47.635 --> 23:48.751
I'm sorry, Father.

23:49.553 --> 23:51.215
Do you feel His presence, Daniel?

23:51.972 --> 23:53.884
Yes, of course. Always.

23:56.810 --> 23:57.971
It's okay to say no.

23:58.896 --> 23:59.807
Yeah, I know.

24:03.442 --> 24:04.978
Wait a minute. How is it okay?

24:05.069 --> 24:06.651
This isn't magic.

24:06.737 --> 24:07.693
We are not special.

24:07.780 --> 24:12.024
Nor do we have
some privileged access to God.

24:13.410 --> 24:16.528
We are men who chose to serve.

24:17.665 --> 24:20.829
Whether or not we see

24:21.210 --> 24:23.668
or hear or feel Him

24:23.754 --> 24:26.087
at any given time is not the point.

24:27.091 --> 24:29.754
Our job is to be ever present for him.

24:31.178 --> 24:32.259
The day to day,

24:32.888 --> 24:34.095
the minute to minute.

24:35.182 --> 24:36.093
This moment.

24:37.267 --> 24:38.178
Now.

24:38.769 --> 24:39.680
The details?

24:40.437 --> 24:41.427
Exactly.

24:44.984 --> 24:45.895
Do you?

24:46.902 --> 24:47.813
Do I what?

24:48.988 --> 24:50.149
See God?

24:51.865 --> 24:52.776
Yes.

24:55.077 --> 24:56.067
Sometimes.

25:39.121 --> 25:40.453
- A-2.
- Miss.

25:40.539 --> 25:41.780
Really?

25:42.541 --> 25:43.702
I don't cheat at Battleship,

25:43.792 --> 25:45.033
and if I was going to start,

25:45.127 --> 25:46.663
it wouldn't be in this building.

25:47.421 --> 25:48.878
Oh, and, um...

25:50.174 --> 25:52.962
C-6, by the way.

25:55.304 --> 25:57.091
You sunk my battleship.

25:57.181 --> 26:00.174
Oh, three losses in a row.

26:00.684 --> 26:01.720
Ouch.

26:02.227 --> 26:03.559
I wasn't really counting.

26:04.146 --> 26:06.684
Not to be, you know, but I'm...

26:07.608 --> 26:09.816
I'm totally dominating this confession.

26:14.364 --> 26:15.275
What?

26:16.408 --> 26:17.489
You haven't really...

26:18.911 --> 26:22.279
I mean, I don't feel like
I'm really doing my job here.

26:22.372 --> 26:23.829
I know I'm not, actually.

26:23.916 --> 26:25.282
Do you want me to confess something?

26:25.375 --> 26:26.286
No.

26:27.377 --> 26:29.084
I mean, not unless you want to.

26:29.171 --> 26:31.083
I don't want you to feel
like it's required.

26:31.173 --> 26:33.256
There is something.

26:33.550 --> 26:34.461
What?

26:38.764 --> 26:39.845
You can say anything.

26:39.932 --> 26:40.922
I know, but...

26:42.226 --> 26:43.933
I'm just afraid that if I tell you,

26:44.019 --> 26:46.432
I don't know, things might change.

26:46.522 --> 26:48.479
- What things?
- Just... things...

26:48.732 --> 26:49.643
between us.

26:53.112 --> 26:54.023
Jane...

26:55.280 --> 26:57.067
Promise you won't hate me?

26:59.284 --> 27:00.195
I promise.

27:01.328 --> 27:02.239
Thing is...

27:03.956 --> 27:05.538
I've been trying to find a way
to say this all night.

27:05.624 --> 27:07.035
I just... Oh, I don't know.

27:08.168 --> 27:09.079
I...

27:10.546 --> 27:11.457
I...

27:13.423 --> 27:15.335
I totally cheated.

27:17.636 --> 27:18.547
What?

27:19.096 --> 27:20.587
The first game was actually close,

27:20.681 --> 27:22.968
and I just... I lied a bit.

27:23.934 --> 27:26.267
Didn't even place my ships
in the next two.

27:28.689 --> 27:29.679
You hate me?

27:30.524 --> 27:31.435
Why would I hate you?

27:31.733 --> 27:34.851
Just seems like I'm always sitting
on my... you know...

27:35.737 --> 27:38.195
sinner half and...

27:38.991 --> 27:40.402
you have to listen to all of my...

27:42.161 --> 27:43.072
What about you?

27:43.370 --> 27:44.281
Me?

27:45.289 --> 27:46.746
You ever get a chance to sit on this side?

27:46.832 --> 27:48.323
You know, get stuff off your chest?

27:48.959 --> 27:50.666
Priests go to confession, too.

27:51.128 --> 27:54.292
But you only confess
to other priests, right?

27:54.840 --> 27:56.172
That's sort of how it works.

27:56.258 --> 27:58.875
Well, what if you wanted to confess
to someone else?

27:59.720 --> 28:00.676
I don't know what you mean.

28:00.762 --> 28:02.845
To me, for example.

28:03.765 --> 28:06.599
I... don't think that's a very good idea.

28:06.685 --> 28:09.177
It doesn't have to be juicy or anything.

28:09.271 --> 28:10.853
Just something real.

28:12.524 --> 28:15.688
To a normal, non-priesty person.

28:19.281 --> 28:21.068
- Might be good for you.
- I don't think that...

28:21.158 --> 28:23.115
Awesome. Switch me.

28:23.535 --> 28:25.276
Jane? Jane? Jane.

28:30.292 --> 28:31.123
What is this?

28:31.210 --> 28:32.121
It's a gift.

28:32.252 --> 28:33.163
Me to you.

28:33.962 --> 28:34.998
I don't understand.

28:35.088 --> 28:36.295
You go in there, you know,

28:36.965 --> 28:37.796
on the sinner side,

28:37.883 --> 28:40.250
and just for a few minutes
you get to be a normal person,

28:40.344 --> 28:42.427
not somebody
who's gotta do everything right.

28:42.512 --> 28:46.256
not somebody who's supposed to have
any sort of profound existential insights,

28:46.350 --> 28:48.933
and certainly not someone
who's gotta listen to me ramble on

28:49.019 --> 28:49.930
about my...

28:50.771 --> 28:51.761
dying stuff.

28:52.314 --> 28:53.225
Just be you...

28:54.858 --> 28:55.769
Daniel...

28:58.403 --> 28:59.814
with all your Daniel junk.

29:01.865 --> 29:02.776
Come on.

29:04.534 --> 29:05.445
Let's go.

29:40.529 --> 29:41.440
Hmm.

29:43.699 --> 29:48.034
Was kind of hoping that you guys
would have the upgraded side.

29:49.663 --> 29:51.780
Maybe a Tempur-Pedic chair...

29:53.333 --> 29:54.449
flat-screen.

29:55.335 --> 29:57.452
Would it kill you to get
some reading material in here?

29:57.546 --> 29:59.458
- This was a mistake.
- No, it isn't.

30:01.049 --> 30:01.960
Relax.

30:03.552 --> 30:04.463
Relax.

30:06.471 --> 30:08.258
You don't look relaxed. Relax. Breathe.

30:11.643 --> 30:12.633
Good job.

30:13.520 --> 30:14.431
So?

30:16.732 --> 30:17.643
So?

30:19.901 --> 30:20.857
You're gonna make me explain

30:20.944 --> 30:21.809
- this process to you?
- No, I just...

30:21.903 --> 30:22.939
I don't...

30:26.616 --> 30:28.403
- Now, Daniel.
- Hmm.

30:29.494 --> 30:31.360
- My child.
- Mm-hmm.

30:31.455 --> 30:32.445
My lamb.

30:33.457 --> 30:34.573
My lambchop child.

30:37.377 --> 30:38.458
Unburden yourself.

30:40.797 --> 30:41.708
Get absolved.

30:43.925 --> 30:44.836
Speak.

30:45.844 --> 30:46.834
Whatever you want to say.

31:03.320 --> 31:04.231
I don't see.

31:05.447 --> 31:06.733
You don't see?

31:09.576 --> 31:10.487
No.

31:11.870 --> 31:13.987
You don't see what?

31:20.295 --> 31:21.206
God.

31:23.757 --> 31:25.589
God... what?

31:33.809 --> 31:35.516
I don't see God.

31:44.528 --> 31:46.064
I don't think I ever have.

31:54.996 --> 31:56.032
My, uh...

32:01.545 --> 32:02.752
My dad died...

32:04.714 --> 32:06.205
last year, and, uh...

32:09.636 --> 32:12.754
he always liked the idea
of having a priest as a son.

32:13.974 --> 32:16.011
I mean, I liked the idea, too.
Don't get me wrong.

32:16.101 --> 32:18.138
It wasn't like he forced me
into it or anything.

32:18.228 --> 32:19.139
It was just...

32:21.815 --> 32:22.931
just made sense.

32:24.151 --> 32:25.062
You know?

32:27.529 --> 32:29.065
Some kids want to grow up and...

32:29.948 --> 32:32.281
pitch game seven at Yankee Stadium...

32:33.285 --> 32:34.617
give an Oscar speech...

32:35.328 --> 32:38.116
fight fires or terrorists or...

32:39.082 --> 32:39.993
whatever.

32:40.542 --> 32:43.285
I wanted to wear the fancy robes
on Sundays...

32:45.130 --> 32:47.998
give homilies
to captive audiences every week.

32:55.265 --> 32:57.257
Help people.

33:13.867 --> 33:15.654
He never missed a single mass.

33:18.622 --> 33:19.783
Even when he got sick.

33:29.591 --> 33:31.378
He used to tell people that...

33:33.303 --> 33:35.340
he wasn't afraid of death because...

33:38.266 --> 33:40.223
my Danny's got it in with the Big Guy.

33:46.816 --> 33:48.853
Truth is he was never worried though.

33:51.154 --> 33:52.395
He saw Him every day.

33:55.492 --> 33:56.403
But you don't.

33:57.035 --> 33:57.946
No.

34:00.622 --> 34:02.033
So why do you do this?

34:10.422 --> 34:13.916
Because if God ever does show up, I...

34:17.304 --> 34:18.261
I don't want to miss it.

34:31.235 --> 34:34.195
I was sort of hoping for impure thoughts
about the organ lady.

34:34.281 --> 34:35.897
Um...

34:35.991 --> 34:36.902
but...

34:37.909 --> 34:38.820
this'll do.

34:43.665 --> 34:44.576
So what now?

34:47.627 --> 34:49.083
Uh, well...

34:49.963 --> 34:51.670
I guess you could give me a penance.

34:51.755 --> 34:52.667
- Really?
- Yeah.

34:53.507 --> 34:54.543
Nice.

34:55.260 --> 34:56.341
Um...

34:57.596 --> 34:58.962
five Hail Marys,

35:00.181 --> 35:02.844
three Our Fathers...

35:04.394 --> 35:05.475
two...

35:08.690 --> 35:10.556
20 pushups.

35:10.650 --> 35:13.734
And you have to come
to my show next weekend.

35:14.154 --> 35:14.985
Show?

35:15.071 --> 35:17.404
I'm huge in this town.

35:18.325 --> 35:20.658
I'm surprised you're not already
familiar with my music,

35:20.744 --> 35:22.701
but I guess this'll give you a chance

35:22.787 --> 35:25.325
to get hip to what the kids
are into these days.

35:25.415 --> 35:27.372
- Um, I don't...
- Oh, you're totally coming.

35:27.459 --> 35:29.200
I'll save you a seat up front.

35:29.294 --> 35:32.082
I can comp you, but you gotta buy
some coffee or something,

35:32.172 --> 35:33.538
or the owner's gonna get pissy.

35:33.632 --> 35:35.248
- Okay?
- I really don't think this...

35:35.342 --> 35:39.586
Great. I'll give you the details
at our next confession slash date.

35:39.679 --> 35:42.046
Jane. Jane.

35:42.557 --> 35:43.513
Jane!

35:43.600 --> 35:46.308
Yes, you can buy merch from me
directly after the show.

35:46.394 --> 35:48.135
- Jane, I...
- Autographs are fine,

35:48.229 --> 35:50.266
but, please, no photos.

36:16.633 --> 36:17.965
Miss your run again?

36:22.889 --> 36:23.800
Want a muffin?

36:24.683 --> 36:25.639
They're minis, so...

36:26.309 --> 36:28.301
you can have, like, 30 of them,
and they're still not that bad for you.

36:33.274 --> 36:34.435
Why do you do this?

36:40.365 --> 36:41.981
I'm addicted to refined sugar.

36:42.075 --> 36:44.533
It just tastes so darn good on everything,

36:44.619 --> 36:47.111
and if that's a sin, I just figure
I'll work it out on the other side,

36:47.205 --> 36:48.616
but Adam had his apple, and I...

36:50.041 --> 36:51.202
truth be told,

36:51.292 --> 36:54.160
I'm just looking
for one guilt-free sleeve of Oreos,

36:54.254 --> 36:55.711
and I don't think that's too much to ask.

36:57.966 --> 36:59.707
- That's not what I meant.
- I know.

37:03.722 --> 37:04.803
So what...

37:05.390 --> 37:06.301
what's going on with you?

37:07.726 --> 37:08.716
I don't know.

37:08.810 --> 37:12.099
But you're hoping I can offer you

37:12.188 --> 37:14.646
some sort of divine nugget of wisdom

37:14.733 --> 37:17.191
that'll make all the pieces
add up together for you?

37:18.111 --> 37:19.318
What's the story?

37:19.404 --> 37:23.023
Having a crisis of faith or...
something else?

37:23.450 --> 37:24.440
I have faith.

37:27.787 --> 37:31.622
Yippee! Good for you, Father Jamieson.

37:32.167 --> 37:33.078
I just...

37:33.293 --> 37:34.204
I mean, I'm...

37:35.587 --> 37:37.078
I'm just trying to figure it out,

37:37.172 --> 37:38.162
and you...

37:40.467 --> 37:41.298
Forget it.

37:41.384 --> 37:42.374
Did you do the last rights?

37:43.136 --> 37:44.047
What?

37:47.432 --> 37:48.388
When your dad died.

37:50.685 --> 37:52.472
Were you the one
who gave him his last rights?

37:52.562 --> 37:53.518
Yes.

37:55.148 --> 37:56.434
And how did that feel?

37:59.444 --> 38:00.730
He told me it was worth it...

38:02.071 --> 38:03.027
dying...

38:04.616 --> 38:06.482
in order for me to be
the one to anoint him.

38:08.578 --> 38:09.534
What about you, though?

38:13.249 --> 38:14.205
How did you feel?

38:16.169 --> 38:17.330
Gracious?

38:17.420 --> 38:18.410
Did you feel...

38:19.547 --> 38:20.458
blessed?

38:24.719 --> 38:25.630
Just sad.

38:32.519 --> 38:33.851
Go ahead and have a seat, will ya?

38:39.150 --> 38:40.391
Go ahead and take the whole box.

38:42.946 --> 38:44.027
Yeah, they're gluten free.

38:44.948 --> 38:45.904
Organic.

38:49.410 --> 38:50.617
Mostly locally sourced.

38:53.414 --> 38:56.578
Not quite farm to table, but...

38:56.668 --> 38:59.126
...pretty good.

39:07.720 --> 39:10.053
So I've got the second Sunday mass,

39:10.139 --> 39:12.426
a baptism on Saturday afternoon,

39:12.517 --> 39:14.554
and the Monday-morning confession.

39:15.019 --> 39:16.260
Wednesday choir practice

39:16.354 --> 39:18.141
and the Saturday-evening mass.

39:18.231 --> 39:20.097
Oh, and this is pretty fun:

39:20.483 --> 39:22.975
The kids from Sunday school
have asked me to...

39:23.862 --> 39:25.103
to come in and teach a lesson.

39:26.531 --> 39:27.442
You?

39:27.907 --> 39:28.943
Yeah.

39:29.826 --> 39:30.737
It's strange.

39:30.994 --> 39:32.781
It turns out that they find some people

39:32.871 --> 39:35.955
a little more relatable than others.

39:36.040 --> 39:37.872
Well, they're only eight years old, so...

39:39.711 --> 39:41.748
And I will be spending quite a bit of time

39:41.838 --> 39:42.954
over at Ronnie's.

39:43.047 --> 39:44.254
Why not the hospital?

39:45.008 --> 39:46.499
No, that stubborn son of a bitch,

39:46.593 --> 39:47.674
he just refuses to...

39:49.137 --> 39:50.048
let go.

39:51.139 --> 39:53.973
They have moved him home.
He is strictly hospice now.

39:54.559 --> 39:55.800
He's really still alive?

39:56.811 --> 39:57.722
Well, I'll tell you what, Father.

39:58.479 --> 40:01.392
I will let him know that
his selfish need to cling to life

40:01.482 --> 40:03.439
is disrupting your schedule.
How's that sound?

40:03.902 --> 40:05.894
Hmm. How's your week looking?

40:06.613 --> 40:08.104
It's pretty much the same as the last,

40:08.197 --> 40:10.154
except for a few adjustments.

40:10.241 --> 40:11.607
Uh, n-not so fast.

40:12.327 --> 40:15.286
You'll be happy to know that I talked to
the bishop,

40:15.371 --> 40:19.081
and he agreed to drop
the Friday night confessions.

40:19.876 --> 40:23.369
I... It... I just think
that maybe we should...

40:23.463 --> 40:26.376
Well, the church
is going back to normal hours.

40:26.883 --> 40:28.499
Building will close at night.

40:29.385 --> 40:30.501
End of story.

40:31.429 --> 40:32.340
Okay?

40:32.805 --> 40:33.716
Okay.

40:42.231 --> 40:44.769
<i>No, Mom, they don't call mourning
"morning"</i>

40:44.859 --> 40:46.270
<i>because it's supposed to happen every day.</i>

40:46.361 --> 40:47.568
<i>Who told you that?</i>

40:51.699 --> 40:52.610
<i>I know.</i>

40:54.202 --> 40:55.113
<i>I know.</i>

40:57.747 --> 40:59.113
<i>But I don't let it take over.</i>

41:00.333 --> 41:01.949
<i>He wouldn't have wanted us to...</i>

41:04.379 --> 41:06.211
<i>Everything happens for a reason.</i>

41:10.510 --> 41:11.626
<i>I love you too, Mom.</i>

41:13.304 --> 41:14.215
<i>God bless.</i>

43:40.284 --> 43:41.900
One was I couldn't sing harmony,

43:41.994 --> 43:44.611
and the other problem was
I couldn't sing melody.

43:44.705 --> 43:46.241
- So...
- This is me.

43:47.708 --> 43:50.291
Oh... nice.

43:50.378 --> 43:52.370
- Nice.
- Weird, right?

43:52.463 --> 43:53.374
Hmm?

43:53.714 --> 43:55.000
I actually live somewhere.

43:56.717 --> 43:58.003
Now I'm real, too.

43:59.887 --> 44:01.128
Thanks for walking me home.

44:01.430 --> 44:03.342
I always wanted a priest as a bodyguard.

44:04.142 --> 44:05.132
You don't really strike me

44:05.226 --> 44:07.183
as the type of person
that needs protection.

44:07.270 --> 44:08.431
We all need it, Daniel.

44:09.355 --> 44:11.096
The world kinda sucks.

44:11.440 --> 44:12.271
You don't believe that.

44:12.358 --> 44:13.189
No, you don't,

44:13.276 --> 44:14.266
which is why I like you,

44:14.360 --> 44:16.101
but you're also, you know...

44:17.155 --> 44:18.066
you.

44:19.949 --> 44:21.861
Again, confirming my world view.

44:21.951 --> 44:23.067
What's that supposed to mean?

44:23.494 --> 44:24.530
Oh, nothing.

44:24.996 --> 44:27.909
Nothing here. Just a lovely friendship.

44:27.999 --> 44:28.989
What's wrong with that?

44:29.083 --> 44:32.326
Nothing. You're a priest. I'm dying.

44:33.421 --> 44:34.332
I get it,

44:34.589 --> 44:36.706
but in different circumstances,

44:36.799 --> 44:38.210
we're totally dating right now.

44:38.301 --> 44:39.587
No. No, I...

44:41.095 --> 44:43.212
- No.
- Wow, Father,

44:43.681 --> 44:45.673
you really know
how to make a girl feel special.

44:45.766 --> 44:47.428
No, I mean...

44:47.518 --> 44:48.850
this isn't...

44:48.936 --> 44:50.802
I- I... We're...

44:50.897 --> 44:52.229
I... I wouldn't say that...

44:52.315 --> 44:53.726
that... I mean, we're not.

44:53.816 --> 44:55.557
I- I'm not. You know?

44:55.818 --> 44:57.059
